parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission cooling line can cause the transmission to lose motive power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Smoke coming from the rear of the vehicle
transmission fluid leaking from the rear of the vehicle
loss of motive power
erratic tachometer operation
transmission fluid pooling underneath the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electric parking brake can cause abnormal wear and tear on the brake pads and rotors, leading to reduced braking performance and increased risk of accidents.

abnormal wear and tear on brake pads and rotors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the diesel injector can cause engine misfires, leading to reduced engine performance and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Engine misfires
vehicle underpowered while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the DEF tank heater can cause the wiring harness to melt, leading to limp mode and reduced vehicle performance, which can be dangerous when hauling trailers over long distances.
symptoms: Limp mode
wiring harness melting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended vehicle movement can cause accidents or property damage, especially when the vehicle is in park or idle.
symptoms: Vehicle shifting from park to drive on its own
vehicle moving without driver input.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lock-up of the rear wheels can cause loss of control, accidents, or property damage.
symptoms: Rear wheels locking up while driving or accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause the vehicle to pull to one side, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose
the vehicle pulls to one side

the vehicle drifts to the right
the steering wheel can be pulled out of the driver's hand when encountering a pothole.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The tire and alignment issues can cause the vehicle to vibrate, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates at high speeds
the steering wheel vibrates
the tires are out of balance
the vehicle pulls to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the water pump can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage or failure, which can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The temperature gauge indicates overheating
the brake pedal requires excessive force to slow and bring the vehicle to a complete stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the trailering application can cause safety issues while towing, especially in mountainous terrain, as it affects the trailer brakes and can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The app blanks out
displays a black screen
or shows a message that the trailer brakes are disconnected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent radio volume issues can be a distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The radio volume decreases and increases intermittently
with no warning lights illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended activation of the emergency braking system can cause accidents, especially when towing a trailer, and can lead to head-on collisions or rear-end collisions.
symptoms: The emergency braking system activates without warning
sometimes with a message on the driver's information center
and can occur at various speeds
including on side roads and highways.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The service trailer brake system error can cause safety issues while towing, especially if it leads to brake failure, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: The error message "service trailer brake system" appears on the home screen

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel control module can cause the vehicle to not start, which can be a safety issue, especially for emergency responders who need their vehicle to operate reliably.
symptoms: The vehicle won't start

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical/computer problems can cause various safety issues, including unintended brake application, excessive brake pressure, and hot brakes, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The electric parking brake applies itself at certain times
hill start assist also applies itself
excessive pressure is needed to stop the vehicle
brakes smell hot after stopping
and the vehicle was stopped with electric brake problems.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine failure can cause safety issues, especially if it leads to a loss of control or accident.
symptoms: The truck makes a strange noise
the engine light comes on
the truck makes a horrible sound
and oil spits out of the side of the block

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defective brake pads can cause premature wear, leading to a high-pitched squeal, and in some cases, affect the vehicle's ability to stop properly, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: High-pitched squeal or grinding noise when applying the brakes
brakes feel spongy or soft
vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic parking brake system can cause the parking brake to engage unexpectedly, leading to a loss of control or accidents, especially when driving on hills.
symptoms: Warning light on the dashboard
parking brake engages unexpectedly
decreased gas mileage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion in the brake system can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to a loss of control or accidents.

warning light on the dashboard
corrosion on the brake system components.
